% OpenCode CLI profile for a Claude-Code-/simplify-equivalent cleanup pass.
% Reference-only today: `pdd checkup simplify` does not invoke OpenCode yet.

<include>checkup_simplify_workflow_LLM.prompt</include>

<opencode>
## Prerequisites
- `opencode` CLI on PATH (`opencode --version`).
- Authenticated per OpenCode docs (`opencode auth login` when required).

## Suggested invocation pattern (manual / future PDD wiring)
Run inside the candidate worktree with explicit in-scope paths in the prompt body:

```bash
cd "$CANDIDATE_WORKTREE"
opencode run --format json "$(cat /path/to/simplify_prompt.txt)"
```

Adapt flags to your installed OpenCode version; prefer non-interactive, JSON-capable modes so PDD can
parse success, cost, and summary when this profile is wired into `run_checkup_simplify`.

## Model selection
- Honor `OPENCODE_MODEL` when supported by your CLI build.

## Parity notes
- Same allowlist, backup, evidence, and `--verify` selection semantics as the Claude Code path.
- Future PDD integration should reuse `checkup_simplify_workflow_LLM.prompt` for prompt parity.
</opencode>
